cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the integration of physical and virtual worlds to enable ad-hoc socializing of users interested in similar information. This involves the use of location and presence, which are concepts related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social computing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of tacit knowledge and implicit knowledge in crowds, which are related to data mining (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of a proof-of-concept model and empirical analysis, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
